name: Extortion in the third degree
text:
§707-767  Extortion in the third degree.  (1)  A person commits the offense of extortion in the third degree if the person commits extortion of property, labor, or services.
     (2)  Extortion in the third degree is a misdemeanor. [L 1979, c 106, pt of §1; gen ch 1993; am L 2008, c 147, §7]
